results.description:
The most chill dog in the world.

He followed us for quite some distance on Om Beach which is curiously shaped like the Hindu syllable "Om" in the quaint town Gokarna on the western coast of India. The small trek seemed to have taken a toll on this old soul's paws. And just like that, the senior citizen trotted past us and plopped on the beach. He seemed perfectly aware and possibly was very purposeful in picking his spot. And just as he sat down, the first wave crashed into him. Nothing like a cold wave breaking on you on a hot summer day. In the next 5 mins, we joined him.
